body: Addressed here: https://github.com/apache/incubator-superset/pull/3597

Do you have a `superset worker` process running? Is it getting the message from the queue?

Also as you set this up, please fill in any holes there may be in the installation docs and send a PR, that will help the next wave of people get set up.

@mistercrunch I think so? How do i know if the superset worker process is running? In the past when I didnt have the custom config file, the query using async workers would say "Make sure you have a celery process running" or something to that effect. That message doesn't appear with my current configuration

Oh that's different. You have to fire up a `superset worker` command. The assumption is that `superset runserver` and `superset worker` are running on different machines (though they can be running on the same machine no problem). That way you can scale those 2 things independently on as many machines as you need.

Please clarify the docs if you don't mind. They're in the repo under `docs/installation.rst`

Sounds like row level security to me (other issues talk about this). Though the mechanisms for row-level-security would be around enforcing a WHERE clause for people on certain tables, as opposed to enforcing a filter on a dashboard.

@mistercrunch that appeared to be the issue, just some weird naming that confused me a bit I guess.   The config has worker configuration in it, when you run the server it says its launching workers, they're both called superset workers, but they arent the same thing.

It's telling me my results backend isnt configured now, but that should be much easier to figure out
